5. Title of project: (Must be limited to 53 letters and spaces.)
Evaluating CV Nutrition Education in High School
6. Summary of project. (Please try to limit to 250 words. The back of this page may be used to continue the summary.)
We do not know if high school students will voluntarily adopt a cholesterol lowering
diet. We propose to test the ability of a realistic program of nutrition education to
accomplish this change in dietary attitudes and behavior.
The subjects are the tenth grade science students in two high schools. Students from
one school will receive a vigorous, but realistic program of cardiovascular health education
including classroom instruction, student sponsored "rap" sessions and free diet counselling
for student and family. We will examine all students on heart disease knowledge and attitudes
initially and one year later. Students from the Intervention School will be examined also
at three months. In addition male students at both schools will be tested for blood cholesterol
and triglyceride initially and one year later. Students will be notified of results of blood
lipids. . Control students will be referred to their physicians. Intervention student and
families will be strongly urged to participate in the diet counselling program.
